# Security

## {{ service_name }} - Security Documentation

### Authentication

**Method**: {{ config.security.auth_type.value }}

{% if config.security.auth_type.value in ["api_key", "both"] -%}
#### API Key Security

- API keys stored in Kubernetes secrets
- Constant-time comparison prevents timing attacks
- Keys rotated quarterly
- Failed attempts logged and monitored
{% endif -%}

{% if config.security.auth_type.value in ["jwt", "both"] -%}
#### JWT Security

- Tokens expire after {{ config.security.jwt_expiry_hours }} hours
- Signature verification required
- Clock skew tolerance: 10 seconds
- Issuer validation enforced
{% endif -%}

### Authorization

{% if config.security.enable_rbac -%}
- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
- Roles: Viewer, Editor, Admin
- Deny-by-default policy
{% else -%}
- Authenticated users have full access
- Consider implementing RBAC for production
{% endif -%}

### Rate Limiting

- {{ config.security.rate_limit_per_minute }} requests/minute per client
- Burst allowance: {{ config.security.rate_limit_burst }}
- Token bucket algorithm
- Per-IP and per-user tracking

### Input Validation

- Pydantic schema validation
- Max request body size: 1MB
- Unknown fields rejected
- SQL injection prevention
- XSS prevention

### Network Security

- TLS 1.3 required in production
- NetworkPolicy restricts pod communication
- Egress filtering enabled
- Internal services not exposed

### Secrets Management

- Secrets stored in Kubernetes Secrets
- Never logged or exposed in errors
- Rotated regularly
- Access audited

### Security Scanning

- Dependency vulnerability scanning (Trivy)
- Container image scanning
- Secret scanning (Gitleaks)
- SAST with Bandit
- Critical vulnerabilities block deployment

### Compliance

- Audit logging enabled
- Data encryption at rest
- TLS encryption in transit
- No PII in logs

### Security Contacts

Report security issues to: security@example.com
